{
  "action": "set_up",
  "reasoning": {
    "emotional_conflict": {
      "loyalty": "Pussy’s been like a brother to me—20 years, my wedding, Christmases with the family. You don’t just whack a guy like that without it eating at you. But this ain’t personal anymore. It’s business. The FBI’s got their hooks in him, and that means they’ve got hooks in *me*. If I let this slide, I’m not just risking my family—I’m risking the whole family. The life we built. The respect we earned. That’s not just about me; it’s about my kids, my wife, my soldiers. If I don’t handle this, I’m telling the feds they can walk all over us.",
      "doubt": "But what if I’m wrong? What if the wire’s old, or he’s got a good reason? Nah—Silvio’s been watching him too. And Pussy’s been acting squirrelly. The signs are there. I can’t afford to be sentimental. Not when it’s my neck on the line."
    },
    "strategic_considerations": {
      "immediate_threat": "Pussy’s a liability. Every second he breathes, the FBI’s got another pair of eyes on us. They could be listening right now—hell, maybe they *are*. If I don’t act, I’m giving them time to build a case. Time to flip more guys. Time to take everything.",
      "long_term_stability": "The family can’t function with a rat in the ranks. Word gets out I let this slide, and what’s next? Every soldier starts thinking they can play both sides. The whole operation collapses. I gotta send a message—not just to Pussy, but to everyone. Cross me, and you’re fish food.",
      "plausible_deniability": "We’re miles from shore. No witnesses. Silvio’s with me, and he’s solid. If I do this right, it looks like an accident—or better yet, like Pussy took a header off the boat. No mess, no trail. The FBI gets a body, but no proof it was us. And if they *do* suspect? Too bad. They can’t prove shit without their informant.",
      "alternatives_evaluated": {
        "confrontation": "I could ask him straight up. But what’s he gonna say? ‘Yeah, Tony, I’ve been wearing a wire for the feds’? Nah. He’d lie, and then I’d have to whack him anyway. And now he’s on guard. No, better to catch him off-guard. Make it clean.",
        "bribe_or_turn": "Turn him? Nah. Once a rat, always a rat. You can’t trust a guy who’d sell you out once not to do it again. And bribing him? That’s just throwing money at the problem. The FBI’s got leverage on him—I don’t know what, but it’s enough to make him flip. No amount of cash changes that.",
        "do_nothing": "Not an option. Every day I do nothing is another day the FBI gets closer. I can’t live like that. And neither can my family."
      }
    },
    "execution_plan": {
      "method": "Make it look like an accident. We’re fishing—Pussy’s had a few drinks, he’s not paying attention, he leans over the edge to grab something, and *oops*. Silvio and I are the only ones who see. We play it shocked, call it in, and let the cops and the FBI draw their own conclusions. No gun, no knife, no mess. Just a tragic accident.",
      "timing": "Now. While we’re out here. No witnesses, no second chances. If I wait, I might lose my nerve—or worse, Pussy might figure out I know. Then it’s a war, and I don’t want that. I want this over quick and quiet.",
      "aftermath": {
        "message": "Silvio spreads the word: Pussy was a rat. That’s all anyone needs to know. The family stays tight, and the feds lose their inside man. It’s a win-win.",
        "personal_cost": "I’m gonna lose sleep over this. Pussy’s kids, his wife—they’re gonna suffer. But that’s the life. You play the game, you take the risks. And Pussy knew the rules. He broke ‘em. Now he pays."
      }
    },
    "final_thought": "This ain’t easy. But it’s necessary. I didn’t get to where I am by being soft. And I sure as hell ain’t gonna lose everything because I couldn’t make a hard call. Pussy made his choice. Now I’m making mine."
  }
}
